A three-year-old girl was killed in a shooting incident in Eersterivier on Tuesday night. Police said preliminary reports showed three unknown suspects stopped in front of a house at 8.30pm and started shooting randomly. The child was hit in the head and died in hospital, said Brigadier Novela Potelwa. The police's Anti-Gang Unit deployed to the scene found five firearms, including a shot gun, during a search of a nearby house. Two teenagers were among five suspects arrested during the search. The suspects have been charged with possession of illegal firearms. © TimesLIVE